Section 1:
1 L.D. 829
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 JUDICIARY
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 356, L.D. 829, “An Act to Standardize
10 the Laws Regarding the Carrying of Concealed Handguns in State Parks”
11 Amend the bill in the emergency preamble in the 2nd indented paragraph in the 2nd
12 line (page 1, line 4 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "Park," and inserting the
13 following: 'Park and'
14 Amend the bill in the emergency preamble in the 2nd indented paragraph in the 2nd
15 and 3rd lines (page 1, lines 4 and 5 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "and Acadia
16 National Park"
17 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 1.
18 Amend the bill in section 3 in the first line (page 2, line 18 in L.D.) by inserting after
19 the following: "Department" the following: 'of Agriculture, Conservation and
20 Forestry, Bureau of Parks and Lands and Baxter State Park Authority'
21 Amend the bill in section 3 in the 2nd line (page 2, line 19 in L.D.) by inserting after
22 the following: "Lands" the following: 'and the Baxter State Park Authority'
23 Amend the bill in section 3 in the 2nd line (page 2, line 19 in L.D.) by striking out the
24 following: "its" and inserting the following: 'their'
25 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
26 number to read consecutively.
27 SUMMARY
2288 This amendment removes from the bill changes to the laws governing Acadia National
2299 Park. The amendment also directs the Baxter State Park Authority to update its rules to
3300 remove the requirement that a person have a valid permit in order to carry a concealed
3311 handgun in Baxter State Park.
3322 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
3333 (See attached)
